 {"id":"brenner_bot-cxl","title":"Epic: Full-Text Search","description":"Implement super-performant full-text 'search as you type' across all corpus documents.

## Context & Background

Current state:
- Basic search exists but ONLY for transcript sections (236 segments)
- Runtime parsing (no pre-built index) — slow
- No search across distillations, quote bank, or metaprompts
- Missing: debouncing, highlighting, scope filtering

The corpus is ~589KB total (~68k words) across 7 documents. This is ideal for CLIENT-SIDE search — no server round-trips needed.

## User Value

**Primary users**: Researchers looking for specific Brenner quotes, concepts, or passages
**Key scenarios**:
1. 'What did Brenner say about C. elegans?'
2. 'Find all mentions of exclusion testing'
3. 'Compare how different distillations discuss level-splitting'
4. Quick quote lookup for citations

## Goals

1. **Instant Results**: <50ms response time for any query
2. **Search as You Type**: Results update as user types (with debouncing)
3. **Full Corpus Coverage**: Search all documents, not just transcript
4. **Scope Filtering**: Option to search all docs OR just original transcripts
5. **Context Snippets**: Show matching text with surrounding context
6. **Highlighting**: Matched terms highlighted in results
7. **Keyboard Navigation**: Power users can navigate entirely via keyboard

## Anti-Goals

- NOT implementing server-side search (corpus is small enough for client-side)
- NOT adding fuzzy/semantic search (exact matching is fine for v1)
- NOT building advanced query syntax (simple keyword search)

## Technical Approach

**Recommended: FlexSearch** (lightweight, fast, supports partial matching)
- Build index at build time (not runtime)
- Include index in client bundle (~50-100KB compressed for this corpus)
- Use debounced input (150-200ms)
- Virtualize long result lists

Alternative considered: MiniSearch (smaller bundle, similar performance)

## Success Metrics

- Search response time < 50ms for any query
- Index size < 150KB compressed
- Zero perceived latency on type
- Works offline (index is client-side)

## Technical Considerations

- Integration with existing Command Palette (⌘K)
- May extend or replace current transcript-only search
- Index needs to be rebuilt when corpus changes
- Consider lazy-loading index for faster initial page load","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2025-12-29T22:25:48.482839488-05:00","updated_at":"2025-12-30T00:07:26.435067427-05:00","closed_at":"2025-12-30T00:07:26.435067427-05:00","close_reason":"All 7 epic goals met: <50ms search, search-as-you-type, full corpus coverage, scope filtering, context snippets, highlighting, keyboard nav. P2 feature x53 (post-navigation enhancements) can be separate follow-up."}
 {"id":"brenner_bot-d4p","title":"Feature: Search UI/UX","description":"Build the search user interface with world-class UX.

## Rationale

Search UX is critical — it's the primary way users will find specific content in the corpus. Must feel instant, intuitive, and helpful.

## Design Goals

### Visual Design
- Clean, minimal search modal (similar to Linear, Raycast, Notion)
- Keyboard-first but touch-friendly
- Results clearly show document type, section, and context
- Highlighted match terms

### Interaction Patterns

**Trigger Search**
- Keyboard: ⌘K / Ctrl+K (integrate with existing Command Palette)
- Click: Search icon in header
- Mobile: Search button in bottom nav or dedicated search page

**Search Flow**
1. Open search → focus on input
2. Type → results appear instantly (debounced)
3. Navigate results with arrow keys or tap
4. Select result → navigate to that location
5. Matched term scrolled into view and highlighted

**Result Display**
- Document title and type badge
- Section title (if applicable)
- Context snippet with highlighted matches
- Read time / word count indicator

### Scope Filter
- Toggle: 'All Documents' vs 'Transcripts Only'
- Remember user's preference
- Clear indication of current scope

## Integration Points

- Extend existing Command Palette component OR
- Build dedicated search modal
- Add to existing header nav
- Mobile: accessible from bottom nav

## Deliverables

- Search modal/overlay component
- Result list with highlighting
- Scope filter toggle
- Keyboard navigation
- Mobile-optimized search experience

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Search opens via ⌘K and click
- [ ] Results appear within 200ms of typing
- [ ] Can navigate results with keyboard
- [ ] Matches highlighted in results
- [ ] Works well on mobile (touch targets, readable)
- [ ] Scope filter remembers preference","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-29T22:27:11.027347548-05:00","updated_at":"2025-12-30T00:05:51.444651886-05:00","closed_at":"2025-12-30T00:05:51.444651886-05:00","close_reason":"All acceptance criteria met: SpotlightSearch has ⌘K + click triggers, 150ms debounce, keyboard navigation, result highlighting, mobile support. All 4 subtasks closed.","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"brenner_bot-d4p","depends_on_id":"brenner_bot-cxl","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-12-29T22:27:23.885758333-05:00","created_by":"daemon"},{"issue_id":"brenner_bot-d4p","depends_on_id":"brenner_bot-gnj","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-12-29T22:27:25.091958437-05:00","created_by":"daemon"}]}
